# Tool Creation Process

- Follow `docs/tool-creation-process.md` for every new BetLab tool.
- Start by defining explicit inputs, outputs, formulas, and edge cases.
- Implement frontend tool module in `frontend/src/tools`.
- Register tool in both:
  - `frontend/src/data/tools.js`
  - `frontend/src/App.jsx` route table

# Quality and UX

- Validate calculations with representative sample values.
- Ensure tool UX works in both dark and light themes.
- Keep tool components focused; split large logic into `frontend/src/utils` helpers.
- Default numeric inputs to `type="number"` with incremental stepping (`step="1"` unless precision requires another step).
- Apply scoped incrementer styling in `frontend/src/styles.css` and verify in both themes.
- Save notable outputs to history when useful.

# Optional Backend Integration

- If persistence/API is needed, define endpoint contract before coding.
- Mount new routes under `/api` via `backend/src/routes/index.js`.
- Keep success/error JSON shape consistent with backend conventions.

# Completion Checklist

- Frontend build passes.
- No new lint issues in changed files.
- Docs and relevant `.cursor/rules` are updated.
